There is little integrity in this tire shop.  Ever since we had them put on a new set of expensive tires, one of the wheels made a significant noise.  So I took it back to them and they said I was imagining it and sent me away. Using my other mechanic, I validated the noise existed and he recommended I take it back for warranty replacement because of a visible defect.  When I returned to Just Tires the lies and poor service started right away.  Their version of the story changed, the noise existed this time even though they had not even looked at my car again.  But they didn't want to waste anymore time helping me because it would cost them money using an outlandish scenario to prove his point where somehow he loses money on two tires.  Maybe it did cost them in the end, maybe the problem wasn't the tire and it was just a strange coincidence, but I am never going back there because I felt the unwillingness to help my solve my problem was compounded by making me feel like a second class customer. I called in the morning with make of our minivan, model and tire sizes I needed, I spoke with Tony who told me he had 8 of the tires I needed and quoted me $109.00 each "installed", so I gave my Wife the green light to head down there because we had an upcoming road trip, we've used this Just Tires for years with success. Once she arrived the price on the tires doubled to over $200 per tire, I told her, "just leave" and she spoke with Tony while I held on the phone, suddenly, magically the tires were down to $109.00 again. How much profit margin do they have? Later my Wife texted me about an alignment and an oil change, looking at about $540.00 plus tax so I texted her "OK". Then once the car was done there were all these "extras" for valve stems, wheel balance, tire pressure sensors, I spoke with Tony and said, "What happened to the 'installed' price I was told this morning?", he went on to lament how "Goodyear sets the prices" and he has no control over all that. Then the more I spoke to him, and the more my Wife spoke he kept changing the prices. Suddenly the tires were down to $94.99 to absorb some of the balancing and other costs. So he has control or he doesn't have control? I mean which is it?

In the end everything was very shady and we had to confront, kick and scream to get close to what we were originally told. There used to be an employee there named Noel, (not sure I spelled his name right I just remember the name) and he was a much more straight forward person, what he said was what happened and that's why we went back so often. I'll have to see if he is still there and deal with him, if he's at another location and go there, or just find a new place for tires, there are plenty on Tustin. We personally own 8 cars total, plus the inventory that passes through my Dealership that occasionally need tires, brakes, or other work done. I'm sure we can do better than this experience.</review>< Pics>

< username>
Amy Hydock</username>
<Pics>None<//Pics>< Text>
In general, I love taking the train. The food car, the scenery, and the slowed down pace you experience. However, I recommend avoiding any segments of travel by Amtrak buses. I was a bit leery of it, but the agent on the phone said "Oh they are not like greyhound or anything, these are Amtrak buses, very nice." Uh, not really. We left Santa Ana at midnight, or were supposed to. The driver was about 20 minutes late, no big deal I guess, my sister was waiting with my son and I for the train to arrive..and even tho Santa Ana is not the first place I would choose to be around midnite..nothing happened. The problem was after we got on..the bus driver got lost, and there we were, not on a free way or main thoroughfare, but lost, in a "bad" part of Santa Ana. Me and my son..and a few rough looking guys saying they hoped the bus didnt get 'jacked'. The driver announced over the PA system if anyone was familiar with the area and if so could they give him directions.. Fortunately, someone did, and after about 15 -30 minutes, we got back on track. Every segment of our 3 leg trip was late, which I personally do not mind much. However I DO mind being put in danger. When I finally got through to Customer Relations after getting home and spoke with Angela, she said there was no record of the driver getting lost or being late (after about 25 minutes on the phone with her looking through her different "screens'" and explaining that the buses are leased and difficult to get information on. She asked for the bus driver's name, saying they don't even know that.) She actually said the bus arrived early, and there was nothing she could do. I may take the train again, as I have had other good experiences with train only trips, but my recommendation is stay away from the buses. And if anything goes wrong, I would get names and make sure the employees report the problem, be it lateness, getting lost or what have you.< /Text>

<Text>I had a factory maintenance appointment. Hindsight, I suggest calling your service location ahead of time because when you're making the appointment, Hyundai likes to hide the prices.

Appointment was scheduled for 11:45A, though I wasn't helped until around 12:15P, there wasn't much going on that I could see, but again, that I could see, maybe there was a lot going on in the back. There's chips and water while you wait. Pretty pricey for factory maintenance, so I'd suggest putting money on the side a few weeks in advance, so the hit on your wallet isn't too hard and you're able to afford all the suggested maintenance.

I was helped by Raymond, and he was friendly & informative.

The waiting area has a small children's play area with cartoons playing. My little one loved the foam blocks. The popcorn wasn't working. There's vending machines and free coffee to the side, by the restrooms.

There's fast food restaurants just a block away, in case you have a long wait, like myself. Convenient.

I was pretty bummed that my car didnt get washed or vacuumed. It's on the list for the package. I spent over $200 and didn't get all that I paid for. Raymond said I could come back, but honestly, this was my day off, I had already postponed maintenance because it's tough to find the time to go and have things done. 100% inconvenient. I guess I'll have to pay for one of those express washes & vacuum myself, on top of the hour long wait and +$200 I already spent on my car.

My car is working great though, I will say. No complaints about the work that was done.

In comparison, when I had a Honda, service at all of it's locations was always above 5 stars.< /Text>< pics>

Great quality and very friendly service. You can sellect a pizza from their list or, of course make your own.the double crust is a good idea if you are going to load it up. It can get soggy so I get twice baked.
There is a great patio with umbrellas. Lots of parking available. It can take a while if the line is long. Look at pics for menu and details. Please like if helpful.<//text>

<Text>I wanted so much to love this place, as I'm a big fan of Blaze Pizza. The overall experience, although I know today was opening day, was not good. First, I waited 13 minutes in a short line just to order my pizza. There was a staff of 16-17 people I counted but only one person to take the pizza order!? People were indecisive when they turn the corner of the line to be greeted by the order taker (even though I knew exactly what I wanted). One guy literally had to be asked 7+ questions just before they got his first pizza ordered! Then once I was able to order a MINI Ella, it took another 22 minutes to get the pizza. No one checked with me or asked if I wanted anything while I was waiting. Overall, 35 minutes for one mini pizza. It is good but not that good to wait so long. I think they should be taking orders much sooner and get people moved through the line faster and they should talk to the customers more. <Review>Wow! I was hesitant to come here after seeing some of the reviews, but they accepted my medi-cal insurance and I was desperate, and I'm so glad I did!

They verified my insurance over the phone and made sure the Dr. On duty was able to diagnose the issue I was going in for, before I went in, which was really nice.

The reason I went was because I was convinced I had a kidney infection. I looked it up and had every symptom. My general doctor said I probably had Coronavirus and that's what they were going to test me for.... Not my kidney... , so I immediately left and found the Brentwood Urgent care. They saw me within 30 minutes, and the Dr immediately said, It sounds like a kidney infection and was shocked the other Dr would say otherwise. And of course, after tests, it was kidneys!

They gave me an injection of antibiotics and a prescription for antibiotics for the week and I was soooo happy that I had gotten a 2nd opinion! The whole office was so nice and efficient. I am shocked that anyone would give them a bad review! I will definitely be coming here from now on when I have an urgent issue!</Review><pictures>None< /pictures>< Resp>

Clean Facility, knowledgeable Staff
End of December - my husband cut his index finger while slicing a baguette - it was a gusher. We arrived at Brentwood Urgent Care at 7:45 and were greeted  warmly by the staff who remained past closing time help. Wound care supplies were plentiful. The assistant cleaned the wound thoroughly, the doctor glued the cut and applied durable bandages. we left with instructions, supplies and even a follow up call. The finger healed easily. This is the first urgent care facility that I can truly  recommend!< /review>

Cancelled my membership in person back in 2018 when I had to move states. I filled in the form and turned it in. Many months later, I learned that Planet Fitness was still charging my account membership fees. I called the customer service line and they told me that whoever took my cancellation form at this location never put it in their system. Their solution was for me to cancel again. So I tried doing that but I lived hours away from any location and tried sending certified mail which also never worked. I have never dealt with such an enormous headache like this before. I liked the gym and would've rejoined at another location, but they made cancelling into such a pain that I wouldn't recommend Planet Fitness to my worst enemy. Eventually I had to call my bank to flag their withdrawals as fraud. Be careful when cancelling and make sure they send you a confirmation email.<//review>

{'time': 1616678510352, 'text': "Thank you for voicing your concerns, Matthew! Our club was closed as we were adhering to local guidelines. As soon as we reopened, updates were posted to our club page: planetfitness.com/gyms/upland-ca. We always ask that our members keep an eye on our club page that way you all stay in the loop! Additionally, once our club reopens, your normal billing resumes as your membership becomes active. Since you're charged within the terms of your agreement, it is typically non-refundable. However, our club manager would ultimately be your best point of contact for any refund requests!\n\nIf you'd like to cancel your membership, you can either go in person and sign a cancellation form at the front desk with a staff member or you can send a letter by regular or certified mail to our club. You can find our address on our club page that we linked previously. To cancel your membership by regular mail, all you would need to do is place the signed letter in a stamped envelope in your mailbox and the club will handle your cancellation request accordingly. As for the contents of the letter, we ask that you put your name, the reason for canceling, contact information, and your written signature.\n\nIf you have any further questions or concerns, please give our club a call at (909) 297-5090 and request to speak with our club manager. We sincerely hope you'll stay as a member of our PF family but if not, we wish you the best of luck on your amazing fitness journey!"}< /Response>

<Text>I hadn't been to see a dentist in 17 years.   I dont have a particular reason- just never had any pain.  But with that said, All people that are afraid of the dentist should have gone with me today.  I had 2 appointments today.  From the moment I walked in I was helped by some very beautiful young ladies and seated. I was called to meet the ortho and a young- also beautiful woman began to prep me and answered any and all questions I had.   I met the ortho surgeon who was male and also very nice. ( My teeth are drifting apart and I was concerned I would have rotten teeth, unusable for braces  It had been 17 years afterall.)  I was given a good examination by somebody with knowledge. I was deemed good for braces.  I have no money so it's for the future.
My 2nd appt was for a cleaning- I really feared bad news from the dentist.  I was called 10 min after my prior appt. I had x rays done and had to bite on plastic which wasn't so bad I just have a small gag reflex with the plastic throwaway sleeve they cover the biting part with.  The gorgeous young lady that took the xrays was also extremely helpful in any of the Q&A I had.  I was moved to a different room where they would actually do the cleaning.  I met the dentist-  This guy was middle aged and cracking jokes.  He is awesome.  I feared his news after a young woman(also beautiful) came and took different pictures of my teeth and.. dried them.  The dentist saw me and had me open wide, he searched for cavities and other complications and found none- which is awesome! Yay Me!  After sooo long of not seeing a dentist I really didnt expect that.  I try to take care of my teeth but I dont floss.  It was now time for my cleaning.  I think I am like everyone when I say having power tools in your mouth can be quite scary.  But, BUT- they've made leaps and bounds in dentistry since 17 years ago.  The tools are very small and not very noisy.  I braced for some sort of pain while they turned on the tool and started cleaning- there was none.  The most awkward anything was the sensation of the tool doing its job in front and behind my teeth.  My dentist finished cleaning , cracked some more jokes and ran off to some other beautiful smile to help.  A young woman chatted with me while finishing with flouride and asked me to rate them and so I am here!  These guys kick ass, All of em! Everyone that I spoke to or had questions with was genuinely professional,  pleasant, and courteous. ... and beautiful.

I understand that wait times could be different and that you may need more than just a cleaning.  In my experience when you find a good place filled with heartfelt, wonderful people,- it normally stays that way.  This Western Dental has it in spades and I recommend any and all to go and check em out.

Sorry to all at Western Dental in Banning I am extremely horrible with names.  You guys keep kickin ass, I'll see you guys soon :)<//Text>< pictures>
